Given the root of a binary tree, return the inorder traversal of its nodes' values.

Example 1:
Input: root = [1,null,2,3]
Output: [1,3,2]

The Logic: Left -> Root -> Right


class Solution 
{
    public List<Integer> inorderTraversal(TreeNode root) 
    {
       List<Integer> result = new ArrayList<>();

       traverse(root,result);  //Start recursive helper
       return result; 
    }

    public void traverse(TreeNode node, List<Integer> result)    //Helper method to handle recursion
    {
        if (node == null)                  //base case
        {
            return;
        }
        traverse(node.left, result);      //traverse left

        result.add(node.val);             //visit root (add value)

        traverse(node.right, result);     //traverse right
    }
}
